20first%2015%20years%20of%20our%20marriage%2C%20I%20rarely%20had%20a%20great%20night's%20sleep.%20I%20love%20my%20husband%2C%20but%20I%20also%20love%20feeling%20rested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20night%2C%20I%20tried%20really%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhack-fall-asleep-2-minutes-2018-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehard%20to%20fall%20asleep%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Sometimes%2C%20I'd%20pick%20up%20a%20book%20and%20read%20until%20my%20eyes%20got%20heavy.%20If%20it%20was%20really%20bad%2C%20I'd%20lie%20on%20the%20couch.%20I%20would%20get%20some%20sleep%2C%20but%20it%20was%20fitful%2C%20and%20I'd%20wake%20up%20each%20morning%20not%20feeling%20well%20rested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20first%20got%20together%20in%202005%2C%20he'd%20just%20finished%20working%20as%20a%20contractor%20in%20a%20warzone%2C%20so%20I%20expected%20him%20to%20have%20disrupted%20sleep%20based%20on%20that%20experience.%20I%20never%20thought%20about%20going%20to%20bed%20in%20a%20different%20room.%20Sharing%20the%20same%20bed%20is%20so%20ingrained%20in%20our%20culture%20it%20didn't%20occur%20to%20me%20we%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsleep-divorce-same-room-separate-beds-relationship-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esleep%20in%20separate%20beds%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225bb44835-d0ed-44db-b11e-343d536f6c71%5C%22%3EWe%20tried%20other%20remedies%20for%20his%20snoring%20first%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20first%20got%20together%2C%20he%20didn't%20really%20snore%2C%20but%20over%20the%20next%2015%20years%2C%20it%20got%20progressively%20worse.%20To%20say%20I%20was%20sharp%20with%20my%20husband%20in%20the%20morning%20is%20a%20kind%20way%20to%20put%20it.%20We%20would%20jokingly%20say%20I%20woke%20up%20a%20bear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20tried%20a%20few%20different%20remedies%20to%20help%20solve%20the%20problem.%20We%20bought%20a%20king-sized%20bed%20because%20I%20thought%20the%20extra%20space%20would%20help%20with%20his%20tossing%20and%20turning.%20Then%20we%20bought%20a%20sound%20machine%20designed%20to%20mask%20other%20noise%2C%20but%20it%20was%20so%20loud%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20sleeping%20on%20the%20launchpad%20of%20the%20Kennedy%20Space%20Center.%20He%20finally%20got%20into%20a%20sleep%20study%20and%20discovered%20he%20suffers%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fhow-to-treat-sleep-apnea%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esleep%20apnea%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20your%20breathing%20stops%20and%20starts%20while%20you%20sleep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224284%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tami%20Shadduck%20at%20the%20Cardiff%20Castle%2C%20she%20is%20sitting%20outside%20and%20wearing%20a%20denim%20jacket%2C%20grey%20pants%2C%20white%20shoes%2C%20and%20sunglasses.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6687ea10268f62ba18a7a093%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223213%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETami%20Shadduck%20sleeps%20better%20since%20she%20started%20sleeping%20in%20a%20separate%20room%20from%20her%20husband.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20Tami%20Shadduck%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2289f6b215-21ca-4165-8916-13b0f37a3ecf%5C%22%3EI%20first%20slept%20in%20the%20guest%20bedroom%20when%20I%20got%20strep%20throat%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%202020%2C%20I%20got%20strep%20throat%20and%20slept%20in%20the%20guest%20bedroom.%20I%20slept%20like%20a%20grandfather%20after%20Thanksgiving%20dinner.%20When%20I%20recovered%20from%20strep%20throat%2C%20I%20continued%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsleeping-apart-has-helped-our-marriage-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esleep%20in%20the%20spare%20room%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20I%20realized%20I%20was%20sleeping%20much%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20realized%20I%20wanted%20to%20make%20it%20a%20more%20permanent%20move%2C%20I%20started%20by%20verbalizing%20how%20much%20happier%20and%20rested%20I%20felt%20in%20the%20morning.%20I%20think%20it%20took%20my%20husband%20a%20while%20to%20process%20how%20he%20really%20felt%20about%20it.%20But%20we're%20now%20at%20the%20point%20where%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-start-sleeping-in-separate-beds-sleep-divorce-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esleeps%20better%20alone%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20too%2C%20because%20he's%20not%20worrying%20about%20keeping%20me%20awake.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22834b3a82-cc68-4311-aa39-aa81f49a50d8%5C%22%3EWe%20shared%20our%20sleeping%20arrangements%20with%20others%20and%20were%20surprised%20by%20the%20reaction%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20a%20vague%20idea%20that%20some%20other%20couples%20also%20slept%20apart%20but%20didn't%20know%20anyone%20personally%2C%20so%20we%20decided%20to%20keep%20the%20fact%20that%20we%20slept%20in%20separate%20bedrooms%20to%20ourselves.%20When%20we%20finally%20told%20friends%20and%20family%2C%20it%20felt%20empowering.%20We%20were%20surprised%20by%20how%20many%20people%20said%20they%20wished%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexperts-say-partners-sleeping-in-separate-beds-isnt-great-for-intimacy-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eslept%20apart%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20friends%20had%20situational%20experiences%20of%20sleeping%20separately%20due%20to%20having%20young%20children%20or%20being%20sick%2C%20so%20it%20was%20easy%20for%20them%20to%20relate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20may%20think%20their%20love%20lives%20will%20suffer%20if%20they%20decide%20to%20sleep%20in%20separate%20beds%2C%20but%20that%20isn't%20the%20case.%20Intimacy%20happens%20in%20a%20thousand%20little%20moments%20throughout%20the%20day.%20To%20me%2C%20sleep%20is%20a%20health%20behavior%2C%20and%20intimacy%20is%20part%20of%20a%20healthy%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20really%20grateful%20my%20husband%20is%20interested%20in%20my%20health%20and%20happiness%2C%20not%20some