ts-new-records-with-polaris-dawn-mission%2Farticleshow%2F111534286.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Massive%20Asteroid%20Heading%20Towards%20Earth%20At%2065%2C000%20Kmph%2C%20Warns%20NASA%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EA%20massive%20asteroid%2C%20named%202024%20MT1%2C%20is%20hurtling%20towards%20Earth%20at%20an%20astonishing%20speed%20of%2065%2C215%20km%2Fh%2C%20warned%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcneos.jpl.nasa.gov%2Fca%2F%C2%A0%5C%22%3ENASA%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20asteroid%2C%20measuring%20approximately%20260%20feet%20in%20diameter%2C%20is%20as%20big%20as%20the%20Statue%20of%20Liberty%20in%20size.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20asteroid%20is%20expected%20to%20make%20its%20closest%20approach%20to%20Earth%20on%20July%208%2C%20passing%20at%20a%20distance%20of%20approximately%201.5%20million%20km%20from%20our%20planet.%20This%20is%20about%20four%20times%20the%20distance%20between%20Earth%20and%20the%20Moon.%20Asteroids%20of%20this%20size%20are%20considered%20potentially%20dangerous%20because%20they%20could%20cause%20significant%20damage%20if%20they%20were%20to%20collide%20with%20Earth.%3Ca%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fetimes%2Ftrending%2Fasteroid-as-big-as-the-statue-of-liberty-heading-towards-earth-at-65215-kmph-nasa%2Farticleshow%2F111512174.cms%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1720336142351000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw3zLx58NAOnXt461sFc8iiD%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fetimes%2Ftrending%2Fasteroid-as-big-as-the-statue-of-liberty-heading-towards-earth-at-65215-kmph-nasa%2Farticleshow%2F111512174.cms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAsteroid%202024%20MT1%20was%20first%20detected%20by%20NASA's%20Near-Earth%20Object%20Observations%20Program%2C%20which%20tracks%20and%20characterises%20asteroids%20and%20comets%20that%20come%20close%20to%20Earth.%20The%20program%20uses%20ground-based%20telescopes%20and%20radar%20systems%20to%20monitor%20these%20objects.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ECurrently%2C%20NASA's%20Jet%20Propulsion%20Laboratory%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fssd.jpl.nasa.gov%2Ftools%2Fsbdb_lookup.html%23%2F%3Fsstr%3D2024%2520MT1%5C%22%3EJPL%3C%2Fa%3E)%20in%20Pasadena%2C%20California%2C%20is%20closely%20tracking%20the%20asteroid's%20trajectory.%20JPL's%20Asteroid%20Watch%20dashboard%20provides%20real-time%20data%20on%20the%20asteroid's%20position%2C%20speed%2C%20and%20distance%20from%20Earth.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWhile%20there%20is%20no%20immediate%20threat%20of%20collision%2C%20NASA's%20Planetary%20Defense%20Coordination%20Office%20(PDCO)%20is%20actively%20working%20on%20strategies%20to%20mitigate%20such%20threats.%20The%20PDCO%20collaborates%20with%20international%20space%20agencies%20and%20research%20institutions%20to%20develop%20technologies%20for%20asteroid%20deflection%20and%20impact%20prevention.%20One%20key%20technology%20being%20explored%20is%20the%20Double%20Asteroid%20Redirection%20Test%20(DART)%20mission%2C%20which%20aims%20to%20test%20the%20feasibility%20of%20deflecting%20an%20asteroid%20by%20crashing%20a%20spacecraft%20into%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20close%20approach%20of%20asteroid%202024%20MT1%20has%20sparked%20interest%20among%20astronomers%20and%20space%20enthusiasts.%20Observatories%20worldwide%20are%20gearing%20up%20to%20capture%20images%20and%20data%20of%20asteroid%202024%20MT1.%20Researchers%20aim%20to%20study%20its%20composition%20and%20structure%20to%20gain%20insights%20into%20the%20early%20solar%20system%20and%20planet%20formation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720255980000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2Fun15ft5k_asteroid-generic_625x300_06_July_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nd